==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mercurialist
<hw>Mer*cu"ri*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One under the
influence of Mercury; one resembling Mercury in character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A physician who uses much mercury,
in any of its forms, in his practice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mercurialize</ent>⟦br⟧
